# Create app manifest and setup docs

Create Slack app manifest YAML and documentation for deploying the integration.

## Requirements

- [x] Create `config/slack_manifest.yml` (~100 lines)
- [x] Define all required OAuth scopes
- [x] Configure event subscriptions and slash commands
- [x] Add setup guide to `docs/integrations/slack.md` (~150 lines)
- [x] Document environment variables and secrets
- [x] Include ngrok/tunneling instructions for development

## Acceptance Criteria

- [x] Manifest includes all required features and scopes
- [x] Event subscriptions configured for message and app_mention
- [x] Slash commands defined (`/pag`)
- [x] Interactive components enabled
- [x] Documentation covers app creation and installation
- [x] Development setup instructions tested

## Context

**Plan References**:
- `.plan/2026-02-05-velvet-cascade/integrations.md` lines 279-286 (Slack features)

**Key Points**:
- App manifest allows one-click app creation
- Request URL must be publicly accessible (ngrok for dev)
- Event subscriptions require signature verification
- Slash commands can be workspace-specific or global

## Notes

Required event subscriptions:
- `message.channels` - Channel messages
- `message.groups` - Private channel messages
- `message.im` - Direct messages
- `app_mention` - @mentions

Slash command configuration:
- Command: `/pag`
- Request URL: `https://your-domain.com/slack/commands`
- Short description: "Interact with PAG agent"
- Usage hint: `ask [question] | fork | stats`

Manifest template structure:
```yaml
display_information:
  name: PAG Agent
  description: 24/7 LLM agent orchestration
features:
  bot_user:
    display_name: PAG
  slash_commands:
    - command: /pag
      description: Interact with PAG agent
oauth_config:
  scopes:
    bot: [chat:write, commands, users:read, channels:read]
settings:
  event_subscriptions:
    request_url: https://your-domain.com/slack/events
    bot_events: [message.channels, app_mention]
```
